00:07:28.690 --> 00:07:32.045
drives some of our decisions to quit,
but sometimes other things

142
00:07:32.045 --> 00:07:36.272
happen in our lives that make us decide to
move that has very little to do with that.

143
00:07:36.272 --> 00:07:41.195
And so any one explanation of it's
probably only gonna explain what

144
00:07:41.195 --> 00:07:44.050
goes on for fairly small number of people.

145
00:07:44.050 --> 00:07:47.310
And so, you're gonna there are people
who love their job but quit anyway.

146
00:07:47.310 --> 00:07:49.990
And there are people who hate their
job but when they go out, and

147
00:07:49.990 --> 00:07:53.360
compare it with alternatives they decide
that there's nothing better that they

148
00:07:53.360 --> 00:07:55.000
can do,and they stay.

149
00:07:55.000 --> 00:07:59.040
A third way in which people think
about this process of leaving,

150
00:07:59.040 --> 00:08:03.390
is basically in terms of search, and
so this very much comes from economics

151
00:08:03.390 --> 00:08:06.920
where people think there are lots of
different jobs that we could be doing,

152
00:08:06.920 --> 00:08:10.120
and we're gonna enjoy those
jobs to a different extent

153
00:08:10.120 --> 00:08:14.350
based on how well they fit our preferences
and also how good we are at them.

